{"key":"processedPost-7618169","value":{"id":7618169,"first":7617900,"last":7621649,"when":1194716168,"utime":"11/10/07 07:36 PM","content":"Depending on the BTU's, you might want to run your burner at under full throttle if you're using plastic spawn bags.  The flames that curl around the bottom of the PC and up the sides can melt bags that are touching the walls.  This isn't a problem with electric burners where the heat is conducted directly to the bottom, but the convection heat of a gas burner can cause this problem.  Other than that and of course the obvious oxygen requirements that I'm sure you're aware of, it should work fine.<br />RR","title":"Re: Any one used a gas fryer pot burner to heat a pc???","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}